name: shop
description:
Based on your complaints of not having good enough equipment, your company is giving you a budget of N dollars to buy whatever you want. Given a list of prices from the store, determine the maximum number of pieces of equipment you can buy from that store.

Input from stdin:

One line containing the integers N and M (where N is the budget and M is the number of elements in the list) followed by M integers consisting in the prices of the equipment

Output into stdout:

One number representing the maximum number of pieces of equipment you can buy

Restrictions

M < 1000000, N is a 32 bit unsigned integer; the costs are 32 bit unsigned integers
